1. docs.docker.com
2. To view the version of ubuntu

cat /etc/*release*

3. Uninstall any older version of Docker from Ubuntu system
$ sudo apt-get remove docker docker-engine docker.io containerd runc

4. Set up repository and install the software

• Using the convinience script

$ curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com -o get-docker.sh // downloads the script docker.sh
$ sudo sh get-docker.sh

5. check the version of docker

$ sudo docker version

6. Install a simple container to see if docker is set up correctly

• https://hub.docker.com/
• pickup container command for whalesay

sudo docker run docker/whalesay cowsay Hello-World!